Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the
rice. When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.
Drain in a #sieve{} and return to the #pot{}, cover with a #lid{} until ready to
serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(halved and chopped into small
pieces) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Halve the @Green Chilli{½} lengthways, deseed then finely
chop.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{}. Once hot, add the
@Diced Chicken Thigh{260%g} and stir-fry until turning golden, ~{3-4%mins}.
Add the onion and continue to cook, stirring, until the onion is softened,
~{2-3%mins}.

Add the @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, garlic, half the green chilli (add less if you
don't like heat!), and @Tomato Puree{30%g}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%min}, add
the @Tomato Passata{1%400ml can}, @Water{100%ml} and @Chicken Stock Powder{1%tbsp}
and bring to a simmer. Season with salt and pepper and simmer until thickened,
~{6-8%mins}. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Coriander{1} (stalks and all).

Add the @Baby Spinach{100%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until it's
wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}. Simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly,
the chicken is cooked and the flavours have developed, ~{3-4%mins}. IMPORTANT:
The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Stir the
@Mango Chutney{40%g} and half the coriander through the curry. Taste and
season with more salt and pepper if you like.

Stir the remaining coriander through the rice. Divide the rice and curry
between your #bowls{}. Top with the remaining green chilli. Enjoy!